{"questionId":"ffdaaea2-8ec1-44b7-903d-084c644b881a_11","correctAnswer":"D","section":"Math","steps":[{"title":"Set up","content":"Find $c$. Since $p(x)=8x+b$ and $p(4)=38$: $32+b=38$, so $b=6$ and $p(x)=8x+6$. Then $p(c)=-2$: $8c+6=-2$, so $c=-1$."},{"title":"Solve","content":"Now use $t(-1)=-3$ and $t(5)=51$ to find slope: $m=\frac{51-(-3)}{5-(-1)}=\frac{54}{6}=9$."},{"title":"Answer","content":"<strong>D</strong> is correct."}]}